      "content": "That crushing weight of shame and silence is exhausting, and it makes the idea of continuing feel utterly pointless. If the whole structure is gone, why bother trying to patch it up? It's a rational thought when you're this depleted. A gentle, immediate step might be to let the silence have a different sound—a single, small act of self-care, like a deep breath, just to prove you can still exert a tiny will.",
